    <section class="signal-strip" aria-label="Clipency capabilities">
      <span>Creator Distribution</span>
      <span>Campaign Intelligence</span>
      <span>Proof Review</span>
      <span>Payout Visibility</span>
      <span>Performance Marketing</span>
      <span>Modern Attention</span>
    </section>

    <section class="section system-section" id="system">
      <div class="section-heading center reveal">
        <div class="eyebrow">WHAT CLIPENCY IS</div>
        <h2>A distribution system for campaigns that need momentum.</h2>
        <p>
          Most campaigns do not fail because the idea is weak. They fail because execution is scattered. Clipency gives brands and creators a single workflow from campaign brief to verified output.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="system-grid">
        <article class="system-card large reveal">
          <span class="card-number">01</span>
          <h3>Campaigns become structured</h3>
          <p>
            Every campaign can carry its goal, platforms, category, payout logic, submission rules and review status. The result is a clean distribution brief that creators can act on.
          </p>
          <div class="card-line"></div>
        </article>

        <article class="system-card reveal delay-1">
          <span class="card-number">02</span>
          <h3>Creators become operators</h3>
          <p>
            Clippers discover campaigns, publish content, submit proof links and track their performance inside one creator workspace.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="system-card reveal delay-2">
          <span class="card-number">03</span>
          <h3>Proof becomes visible</h3>
          <p>
            Submissions, views, status, notes and approvals become traceable instead of being buried in screenshots and chats.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="system-card wide reveal delay-3">
          <span class="card-number">04</span>
          <h3>Teams get operating clarity</h3>
          <p>
            Clipency is designed to reduce manual coordination and make creator-led campaigns easier to review, approve, repeat and scale.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section clients-section" id="clients">
      <div class="split-copy reveal">
        <div class="eyebrow">FOR CLIENTS</div>
        <h2>Built for brands that want attention with accountability.</h2>
        <p>
          Clipency helps campaign teams move beyond vague influencer promises. Brands get a structured way to brief creators, collect proof, review submissions and understand campaign movement.
        </p>

        <div class="pill-row">
          <span>Music promotion</span>
          <span>Brand awareness</span>
          <span>Product launches</span>
          <span>Creator distribution</span>
          <span>Performance review</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="comparison-panel reveal delay-1">
        <div class="comparison-row muted">
          <span>Without a system</span>
          <strong>Campaigns become scattered DMs, screenshots, missed updates and unclear accountability.</strong>
        </div>

        <div class="comparison-divider"></div>

        <div class="comparison-row">
          <span>With Clipency</span>
          <strong>Campaigns become a workflow: brief, creator, proof, approval and payout.</strong>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section creators-section" id="creators">
      <div class="section-heading reveal">
        <div class="eyebrow">FOR CREATORS</div>
        <h2>A creator workspace designed around output.</h2>
        <p>
          Clippers are not treated like employees or traditional influencers. They are distribution partners who discover campaigns, submit proof and earn through measurable contribution.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="creator-console reveal delay-1">
        <div class="creator-card active">
          <span>01</span>
          <strong>Discover campaigns</strong>
          <p>Find campaigns that match your content style, platform and momentum.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="creator-card">
          <span>02</span>
          <strong>Submit proof</strong>
          <p>Upload post links for review and campaign tracking.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="creator-card">
          <span>03</span>
          <strong>Track performance</strong>
          <p>See views, approved earnings, pending review and active campaigns.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="creator-card">
          <span>04</span>
          <strong>Build reputation</strong>
          <p>Better output can create better campaign fit over time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section proof-section" id="proof">
      <div class="section-heading center reveal">
        <div class="eyebrow">WHY THIS MATTERS</div>
        <h2>The internet rewards campaigns that travel.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="insight-grid">
        <article class="insight-card reveal">
          <span>Insight 01</span>
          <h3>Attention is fragmented</h3>
          <p>
            Distribution now happens through clips, edits, short-form posts, communities and micro pockets of attention. Clipency is built for that world.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="insight-card reveal delay-1">
          <span>Insight 02</span>
          <h3>Proof matters more than noise</h3>
          <p>
            Brands need to know who posted, where it moved, what was submitted and what deserves approval.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="insight-card reveal delay-2">
          <span>Insight 03</span>
          <h3>Creators need clearer earning paths</h3>
          <p>
            When requirements, links, status and payout logic are clear, creators can focus on creating distribution.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section testimonials-section">
      <div class="section-heading center reveal">
        <div class="eyebrow">TRUST SIGNAL</div>
        <h2>Designed to feel serious before the first call.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="testimonial-grid">
        <article class="testimonial-card featured reveal">
          <p>
            “Clipency does not sell vague influence. It creates a clean operating layer around creator distribution, proof and performance visibility.”
          </p>
          <div>
            <strong>Brand Partner</strong>
            <span>Creator Distribution Campaign</span>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="testimonial-card reveal delay-1">
          <p>
            “The creator journey is simple: discover a campaign, publish content, submit proof and track progress.”
          </p>
          <div>
            <strong>Clipper</strong>
            <span>Creator Network</span>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="testimonial-card reveal delay-2">
          <p>
            “The value is operational clarity. Fewer scattered links, cleaner reviews and a better campaign rhythm.”
          </p>
          <div>
            <strong>Growth Team</strong>
            <span>Campaign Operations</span>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section team-section" id="team">
      <div class="section-heading reveal">
        <div class="eyebrow">TEAM</div>
        <h2>The people building the distribution layer.</h2>
        <p>
          A department-wise team showcase for the people behind Clipency. Social profiles can be connected as the public team page expands.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="department-block reveal delay-1">
        <div class="department-title">Leadership</div>

        <div class="team-grid leadership-grid">
          <article class="team-card">
            <div class="team-avatar">S</div>
            <h3>Smit Bharat Patil</h3>
            <p>Technology & Platform</p>
            <div class="team-links">
              <a href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>
              <a href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram</a>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="team-card muted">
            <div class="team-avatar">+</div>
            <h3>Leadership Member</h3>
            <p>Strategy, partnerships and execution.</p>
            <div class="team-links">
              <a href="#">Profile</a>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="department-grid reveal delay-2">
        <article class="team-card muted">
          <div class="department-title">Technology</div>
          <div class="team-avatar">T</div>
          <h3>Technology Team</h3>
          <p>Frontend, backend, product systems and platform reliability.</p>
          <div class="team-links">
            <a href="#">LinkedIn</a>
            <a href="#">GitHub</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="team-card muted">
          <div class="department-title">Marketing & Growth</div>
          <div class="team-avatar">M</div>
          <h3>Growth Team</h3>
          <p>Campaign strategy, creator acquisition and distribution growth.</p>
          <div class="team-links">
            <a href="#">LinkedIn</a>
            <a href="#">Instagram</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="team-card muted">
          <div class="department-title">Operations</div>
          <div class="team-avatar">O</div>
          <h3>Operations Team</h3>
          <p>Finance, legal, approvals, payouts and campaign governance.</p>
          <div class="team-links">
            <a href="#">LinkedIn</a>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section contact-section" id="contact">
      <div class="contact-copy reveal">
        <div class="eyebrow">START WITH CLIPENCY</div>
        <h2>Tell us what you want to move.</h2>
        <p>
          Share your campaign goal, budget range and target direction. Your inquiry enters the Clipency client pipeline and will later reflect inside the admin dashboard.
        </p>

        <div class="contact-points">
          <span>Campaign planning</span>
          <span>Creator distribution</span>
          <span>Proof review</span>
          <span>Performance insight</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <form class="contact-form reveal delay-1" id="landing-contact-form">
        <div class="form-grid">
          <label>
            Full name
            <input name="full_name" required placeholder="Your name" />
          </label>

          <label>
            Work email
            <input name="email" type="email" required placeholder="you@company.com" />
          </label>
        </div>

        <div class="form-grid">
          <label>
            Company
            <input name="company" placeholder="Company / Brand" />
          </label>

          <label>
            Role
            <input name="role" placeholder="Founder / Marketer / Manager" />
          </label>
        </div>

        <div class="form-grid">
          <label>
            Budget range
            <select name="budget_range">
              <option value="">Select range</option>
              <option>$500 - $2,000</option>
              <option>$2,000 - $10,000</option>
              <option>$10,000+</option>
              <option>Not sure yet</option>
            </select>
          </label>

          <label>
            Campaign goal
            <select name="campaign_goal">
              <option value="">Select goal</option>
              <option>Music promotion</option>
              <option>Brand awareness</option>
              <option>Creator distribution</option>
              <option>Product launch</option>
              <option>Other</option>
            </select>
          </label>
        </div>

        <label>
          Message
          <textarea name="message" rows="5" placeholder="Tell us about the campaign, audience, platforms and timeline."></textarea>
        </label>

        <button type="submit" class="magnetic">Submit campaign inquiry</button>
        <p id="contact-form-message" class="form-message"></p>
      </form>
    </section>
  </main>

